  "texts": [
    "Future studies should focus on combining these advanced models with more explainable AI techniques to better understand how specific language features contribute to FTD detection.",
    "Additionally, exploring the model's performance on more diverse and noisy datasets, such as social media text, could further improve its robustness and clinical applicability (Sarzynska-Wawer et al., 2021).",
    "The study by Akbik, Blythe, and Vollgraf (2018) aims to improve sequence labeling tasks, such as Named Entity Recognition (NER) and part-of-speech (PoS) tagging, by introducing a new form of contextualized embeddings called \"contextual string embeddings.\"",
    "Traditional word embeddings, while effective, fail to fully capture the polysemous and context-dependent nature of words, which hinders their performance in sequence labeling tasks.",
    "The objective of this study is to propose a novel approach that models words as character sequences and contextualizes their embeddings based on surrounding text."
  ],
